****** Sample Restriction ******

/*
All of my results are based on a selected sample of LSAC households that satisfy several criteria.

(1) Included households are intact over the observed period (i.e. only stable two-parent households). 
(2) All children are biological; there are no adopted children and no step-parents.
(3) All selected children are at least 10 years old during the fourth wave of the LSAC, because I need access to an initial NAPLAN score observation. 
(4) All selected children have an observed NAPLAN score in 2010 and following waves.
(5) I keep only data observations for selected children whose age is between 10 and 15 at the interview date for waves 4 through
6.
*/

* Count sample size

********** Cognitive Skill Production

use export_bp, clear

xtset cid age

sort cid age

bysort cid (age): gen read_f = read[_n+1] if inrange(_n, 1, 3)
bysort cid (age): gen num_f = num[_n+1] if inrange(_n, 1, 3)
bysort cid (age): gen write_f = write[_n+1] if inrange(_n, 1, 3)

* Step 1: Count the number of distinct age values per cid
bysort cid: egen num_periods = total(inlist(age, 1, 2, 3))

* Step 2: Keep only those cids that have observations for all 3 periods (t = 1, 2, and 3)
keep if num_periods == 3

* Step 3: Drop the helper variable
drop num_periods

keep if age ~= .

sort cid age 

********** Make it to weekly measures

***** ROUGHLY

sum schoolmean if inrange(day, 1, 5) & schoolmean ~= . & age == 1, detail
gen schhr = 6.666667 if age == 1 & inrange(day, 1, 5) & schoolmean ~= .

sum schoolmean if inrange(day, 1, 5) & schoolmean ~= . & age == 2, detail
replace schhr = 6.783333 if age == 2 & inrange(day, 1, 5) & schoolmean ~= .

sum schoolmean if inrange(day, 1, 5) & schoolmean ~= . & age == 3, detail
replace schhr = 6.75 if age == 3 & inrange(day, 1, 5) & schoolmean ~= .

replace schhr = 0 if inrange(day, 6, 7) & inrange(age, 1, 3)

xtset cid age
sort cid age

keep if schhr ~= . & hhinc ~= 0

replace schhr = 60*schhr

xtset cid age
xtdescribe

keep cid cohort wave age simean day read num write hhinc hypscore read_f num_f write_f

sort cid age

